Ben Pierce was born so prematurely doctors didn't think he would survive. With a fighting spirit he pulled through, but his eyes struggled to fully develop. A surgery restored his sight, but it left scar tissue, which will continue to grow as he does. Now nine, the Dallas boy will eventually lose his sight completely, doctors believe, but they don't know when, according to The Daily News-Miner. Determined to make the most of the time he has left, Ben, encouraged by his parents, Kit and Heidi, started drafting a Bucket List of the things he wanted to see, before he can no longer see.
